        <abstract> 
<p>Hopes GdeS will publish on subjects discussed in his letter [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">10587</hi>]. CD had noted similar persistence of variation in fossil shells.</p>  
<p>Calls his attention to Nägeli’s work on <hi rend="italic">Hieracium</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Expresses skepticism about O. Heer’s view that dicotyledonous plants developed suddenly. Believes they must have developed slowly in some part of the globe completely isolated from other regions.</p>
        </abstract>
